Have you ever made a vision board or written down goals only to feel disappointed that those dreams didn’t come true? I want to teach you all of these tools and help as many people as possible step into their power. 
Starting 12/27 I’m hosting a free challenge #beyondthemovement to help you set up your 2023 for success. The way you end your year matters and if you’re interested in learning some hacks that are WAY more effective than a vision board, I’ve gotchu! All the Deets in stories 🙌🏽🤍✨

Did you hear? 👂⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
I’m hosting one more FREE Challenge before we close out 2022 🥳⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Come experience Beyond The Movement on December 27-29 and end the year with intention. ⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
This challenge is the quick yet transformative, dip your toes in intro, into the inner development piece that is a huge pillar in the Yoga Standard model. It’s the thing that gets us to where we want to go. And yes, that means no (physical) movement required, unless you want to of course 💁‍♀️⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Inner development is the internal work (that most of us were never taught) that is required to really experience a big shift in our lives. It’s less about just “doing the thing” and more about the intention, mindset, and devotion behind it. Ever wonder why you roll your eyes when someone says “just do it” (sorry Nike)? As if it’s THAT simple. ⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Sometimes the reason we can’t just “do it” or keep consistent with it is because we might need a bit of pre-work to prep us. We might need to adjust our mindset. We might need to get clear on “why” we’re doing it. We might need to let go of old stories. ⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
The thing is: humans are very nuanced and once we understand that there’s different ways to approach a goal to set us up for success, we start to release the shame about not getting it right the first time (or even second & third) and start to experiment with what our individual needs are. ⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
So I designed this challenge for a few reasons:⁣⁣
1) I understand and have witnessed the power of this type of work and how it directly relates to our quality of life. ⁣⁣
2) I want to help you break the “start & stop” cycle and clear the shame around it using the tools and techniques I have to interrupt old patterns & get unstuck.⁣⁣
3) I want to help you go BEYOND the physical and reach your goals with an overarching sense of fulfillment.⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Ready to try something different? Join me for 3 days inside our Pop-Up Facebook group where I’ll be sharing all the tools and techniques myself and my clients have used to break these cycles and create sustainable transformations ✨⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Link in bio to register for FREE! An email will be sent with all the deets!⁣

3 Reasons why you might be snacking:
☝🏽- You’re too restricted in your new meal plan and you’re truly hungry 👏🏼 ideally listening to your body and making clean snack choices, opting for a healthy pace of weight loss. 
✌🏽- You’re relying on willpower and surface level reasons to eat healthy. I.e., “I want to fit in my old jeans” VS “I’ll show up for myself and others more fully when my body is vibrant & at its potential”
THREE- (unpopular opinion) You’d rather snack than process a negative emotion. POV - OVER Eating is another addiction for numbing our thoughts and feelings rather than feeling them so they can go away for good. 
☝🏽 this is the one I struggled with most of my life and I have a whole blog post about my journey from emotional eating to intuitive eating and chances are if you’re reading this… you might find it valuable.

Not many of you knew me when I was a mess… codependency, insecurity, disordered eating, addictions; anything to numb what I felt deep down. Over the past two decades, I have learned so many tools and treasures that has filled the gap between where I was and where I am now (and I’m positive I’ll grow even more as I continue my path of healing) Yoga & journaling was a huge part of it along with tons of other somatic techniques to peel back my layers and to remember who I truly am. If I could promise there is one thing you could do TODAY to feel good it’s this… grab a piece of paper and 
free write AKA let it ALL out. 
•set your timer for 10 minutes 
•put your phone on airplane mode
•write without your pen lifting from the paper (it’ll likely be illegible)
•rip that shit up and throw it away 

This is one of many life changing EASY practices of releasing repetitive and unproductive negative emotions that have helped me! 

Bonus- take one of my Flows (in the app) and plant new seeds of intention. 

#selfhealingjourney #yogateacher #innerworkisthebestwork
